RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 1 1M Turf CR: 57. Maiden Claiming Purse 10500. FOR MAIDENS, THREE, FOUR, AND FIVE YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000. Minnesota Bred Claiming Price $15,000. (If management deems it inadvisable to run this race on the Turf, it will be run at a distance of 1 Mil e on the main track.) (Rail at 15 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BIG PETE raced in the two path around the first turn, chased the leader on the outside up the backstretch, continued around the far turn still in the two path, began a bid in upper stretch and dueled between horses to get the win. MY CALANTE raced in the middle of the pack between horses through the opening half mile, began a bid from the three path coming around the far turn and dueled on the outside to get up for the win. THREE ROUGH SHODS trailed the field the first time by, improved position while racing in the three path around the first bend, began a bid racing in the two path around the far turn and made a late outside charge in the final furlong to just miss. LUCKY'S LANE saved ground early, tracked the pace setter on the inside up the backstretch, continued to save ground around the far bend and finished evenly. LEAOFLITTLEFAITH led the field while saving ground around the first turn and up the backstretch, came around the second bend in the two path, dueled in upper stretch and weakened in the final furlong. FOREVER INDIAN saved ground early, settled in the middle of the pack on the inside for the run up the backstretch, continued to save ground around the far turn and never threatened. JUST BECAUSE raced in the middle of the pack on the outside through the opening half mile, navigated the far turn from the three path and faded in the stretch. WATER TO WINE raced in the two path around the first turn, trailed the field up the backstretch, saved ground around the second turn and made no bid.

TAKING CHARGE DESI raced off the pace on the inside up the backstretch, continued around the turn in the three path and made no bid.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: SILVER DASH raced in the middle of the pack on the outside for the run up the backstretch, came around the turn in the three path, began a bid passing the quarter pole and edged clear in the final furlong. MIDNIGHT ROYAL trailed the field through the opening quarter of a mile, saved ground around the bend, began a bid nearing the quarter pole and gained ground late. BIRDIE MACHINE tracked the leader on the outside up the backstretch, navigated the bend from the two path, drifted out entering the stretch, bumping with BIG BOY MCCOY in the process, and gained ground late from there. RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 5 7 1/2F Turf CR: 82. Allowance Purse 32000. FOR MN-BRED THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR TRIAL OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. (If management deems it inadvisable to run this race on the tur f, two-year-old races will be run at 6 and 1/2 furlongs and races for three-year-olds and up will be run at a distance of 1 mile on the main track.) (Rail at 15 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BUBBA BOB raced in the two path around the first turn, chased the leader up the backstretch, began a bid from the two path coming around the far turn and kicked clear while drifting out mildly in the lane. PROTONIC AND GIN bumped with the horses to both sides leaving the gate, saved ground around the first turn, settled off the pace on the inside for the run up the backstretch, came around the far bend in the three path, began a bid passing the quarter pole, bumped lightly with MYSTIFIER in upper stretch and gained ground late from there. MYSTIFIER raced in the two path early, continued up the backstretch off the pace between horses, began to move up while racing in the four path around the second turn, drifted in in upper stretch, bumping with PROTONIC AND GIN in the process and gained ground to the wire. NORTH ARM BAY bumped with the horse to his outside at the gate, saved ground around the first turn, raced in the middle of the pack on the inside for the run up the backstretch, continued to save ground around the far bend and finished evenly. SMART OXIE raced in the middle of the pack on the outside through the opening half mile, came around the far turn in the two path and showed no kick. COLOR ME LEGENDARY led the field while saving ground around the first turn and up the backstretch, dueled from the rail around the second bend and in upper stretch and faded in the final furlong. BURNING LEAVES bumped with the horse to his inside at the start, raced off the pace on the outside through the opening half mile, moved up from the three path headed into the far turn, was cut off entering the stretch and stumbled when MYSTIFIER drifted into his lane and took up from there. THE RIDER OF HORSE FOUR, BURNING LEAVES, CLAIMED FOUL AGAINST HORSE THREE, PROTONIC AND GIN, AND HORSE SEVEN, MYSTIFIER, CITING INTERFERENCE IN UPPER STRETCH. A STEWARDS INQUIRY WAS MADE INTO THE SAME INCIDENT. UPON REVIEW, HORSE SEVEN, MYSTIFIER, WAS DISQUALIFED AND PLACED LAST FOR INTERFERENCE WITH HORSE FOUR, BURNING LEAVES.
